info.name: Campus Bridge API
info.description: Campus bridge API was built to provide easy and safe access to information centers related to campus, such as student data, class schedules, lecturer information, and course data. With the CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) feature, users can easily add, retrieve, update and delete data, helping with data-based administration activities.

item.description:
The "Student" collection is an information bank for processing data on "Student". With the CRUD provided, this collection allows users to access, manage and store student-related information in a college environment easily and efficiently.

**Main feature:**

- Create: Users can create a new student profile with personal information such as name, address, contact and email.
- Read: The "Student" collection provides quick access to read information about a specific student or the entire student list. Users can search, filter and retrieve student data based on certain criteria.
- Update: Users have the ability to update student information, such as changing addresses or updating other contact information. This ensures that student data is always accurate.
- Delete: If necessary, users can delete student profiles from the collection. This action can be useful if a student graduates or withdraws.

item.description:
"The 'Supervisor' API is the core of the management system for tracking and managing relationships between students and their supervisors. This table implements many-to-many relationships, allowing one lecturer to be a supervisor for many students, and vice versa.

With the provided CRUD operations, users can easily:

- Create: Determine the relationship between the lecturer and the students being supervised.
    
- Read (Reading): Access information on the list of students supervised by a lecturer and vice versa.
    
- Update: Change or update relationship details, such as the addition of new students.
    
- Delete: Delete the relationship between the student and the supervisor if necessary.
